  plantName: Deer
  description: The Canadian white tailed deer (Odocoileus virginianus) is a widely
    distributed, highly adaptable herbivore found from British Columbia to Nova Scotia.
    Recognized by their reddish-brown summer coat and white-flag tail, they grow
    to about 1 meter tall and are often found in open areas, agricultural zones,
    and young forests.
